# FORGE_SYSTEM — architecture (this repository only)

This file is used by the **Auditor Protocol** after every 5 commits and by the
**agent** when evaluating Architecture-type hypotheses.

Populate all sections at adoption time. Update when the architecture changes.
Incomplete sections will produce low-quality Auditor reviews.

---

## Module map

Describe the top-level structure. List entry points, core domains, and data flow.

```
Entry points:
  - [e.g. src/main.py — HTTP server, CLI entrypoint]
  - [e.g. src/worker.py — background job consumer]

Core domains:
  - [e.g. auth/ — authentication and session management]
  - [e.g. pipeline/ — data processing pipeline]
  - [e.g. store/ — data access layer]

External integrations:
  - [e.g. PostgreSQL — primary data store (via asyncpg)]
  - [e.g. Redis — session cache (via aioredis)]
  - [e.g. S3 — file storage (boto3)]

Data flow (one sentence per path):
  - [e.g. HTTP request → auth middleware → route handler → store → response]
```

