## Module contracts (coupling rules)

Define what each module may and may not depend on. The Auditor checks whether
commits introduce hidden coupling that violates these contracts.

```
auth/         → may use: store/, config
              → must NOT use: pipeline/, external APIs directly

pipeline/     → may use: store/, external integrations
              → must NOT use: auth/, HTTP handlers

store/        → may use: external integrations (DB, cache)
              → must NOT use: auth/, pipeline/, HTTP layer
```

> Add a row per module. "Must NOT use" is the important half — it defines what
> would constitute architectural regression.

