## Scorecard rationale

Explain why the EVAL_SPEC.md weights were chosen for this project.
The Auditor uses this to judge whether the scorecard still reflects true quality
as the codebase evolves.

```
PERF_SCORE (0.20):
  Measures [benchmark target, e.g. p99 latency of /api/process endpoint].
  Threshold: [e.g. 10.0 at ≤50ms, 5.0 at 250ms, 2.0 at 1s].
  Calibrated on: [date + git SHA of calibration commit].

QUAL_SCORE (0.25):
  Measures [e.g. ruff static analysis — zero violations is the bar].
  Low weight because [e.g. ruff is fast and non-negotiable; violations always fixed same-day].

TEST_SCORE (0.35):
  Highest weight because [e.g. this service is correctness-critical; broken tests = production incident].
  Test suite location: [e.g. tests/]

DEBT_SCORE (0.20):
  Measures [e.g. radon average cyclomatic complexity].
  Debt allowed to grow: No — DEBT_SCORE must never drop below baseline across any commit.
```

